%erg v1
Title: Give every skill a two-word discoverable name and an IDH-themed alias
Created: 2026-04-30
Author: claude

--- log ---
2026-04-30T08:45Z claude created

--- body ---
## Context

Skills currently have a mix of naming styles: one-word opaque (`beat`, `raid`,
`perch`, `smoke`), one-word generic (`verify`, `memory`, `celebrate`), and
two-word descriptive (`pick-ticket`, `end-session`, `nightbeat-report`). There
is no alias system; the canonical name is the only entry point.

The goal: every skill has exactly two names — a two-word descriptive name that
is self-explanatory to a newcomer, and a short IDH-themed alias for fluent daily
use. Both names invoke the same skill. Old names continue to work (backward
compatibility is a hard constraint — muscle memory and docs are not invalidated).

## Naming rules

- **Canonical name**: two words, kebab-case, verb-noun or noun-noun. Must be
  discoverable without prior knowledge of the harness (e.g., `end-session`,
  `pick-ticket`, `night-beat`).
- **Alias**: one short word, themed to the Imperial Dragon register. Evocative,
  not explanatory (e.g., `lair`, `roar`, `hunt`). Not required to be unique
  across projects — unique within IDH is sufficient.
- **Backward compat**: existing names that are already two-word descriptive
  (`pick-ticket`, `end-session`, `verify-gate`, etc.) stay as the canonical.
  Existing single-word names become aliases of the new two-word canonical.

